Note: ========================================
Note: HIR to Regex Generator
Note: ========================================
Note: Generates valid PCRE regex from HIR
Note: Part of the Translation translation system
Note: ========================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/emitter_common.runa" as EmitterCommon
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout

@Reasoning:
Entry point: lowers a regex HIR dictionary into a PCRE-syntax regex
string. The HIR layer represents a regex as a tree of typed dictionary
nodes (alternation, concatenation, quantified, group, char_class,
literal, anchor, backreference, dot); this proc owns the emitter for
the duration of the walk and returns the assembled pattern.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Creates a raw byte-buffer emitter, fetches the root "pattern" entry
from the HIR dictionary, dispatches into generate_node, then extracts
the buffer's contents and destroys the emitter. Returns 0 only if the
HIR contains no pattern entry (in which case the emitter is still
torn down).
@End Implementation

@Security_Scope:
HIR input is trusted (produced by the upstream parser). Returned
pointer ownership matches emitter_raw_get_output - caller takes
ownership of the freshly-allocated output buffer.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_regex_from_hir" takes hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Let emitter be proc emitter_raw_create from EmitterCommon
    Let pattern_key be proc create_string_literal with "pattern"
    Let pattern_value be proc get from Dict with hir, pattern_key
    If pattern_value is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_node with emitter, pattern_value
    End If
    Let output be proc emitter_raw_get_output from EmitterCommon with emitter
    proc emitter_raw_destroy from EmitterCommon with emitter
    Return output
End Process

@Reasoning:
Dispatcher mapping a regex HIR node's "type" string to its
corresponding emitter helper. Centralized dispatch keeps the
serialization of each node type localized to one helper, simplifying
future additions (e.g., named groups, lookahead/lookbehind).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-node guard returns immediately. Reads the node's "type" string,
converts to a C-style string, then performs sequential string_equals
checks against each known node-type tag. The "dot" tag is inlined
because emitting a single '.' (46) is cheaper than a function call.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(k) per call where k = number of node-type tags (currently 9).
Sequential string_equals chain is fast at this scale; a hash table
helps only once the tag count grows significantly.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "generate_node" takes emitter as Integer, node as Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    Let type_key be proc create_string_literal with "type"
    Let type_value be proc get from Dict with node, type_key
    If type_value is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    Let type_str be type_value
    Let is_alternation be proc string_equals with type_str, "alternation"
    If is_alternation is equal to 1:
        proc generate_alternation with emitter, node
        Return
    End If
    Let is_concatenation be proc string_equals with type_str, "concatenation"
    If is_concatenation is equal to 1:
        proc generate_concatenation with emitter, node
        Return
    End If
    Let is_quantified be proc string_equals with type_str, "quantified"
    If is_quantified is equal to 1:
        proc generate_quantified with emitter, node
        Return
    End If
    Let is_group be proc string_equals with type_str, "group"
    If is_group is equal to 1:
        proc generate_group with emitter, node
        Return
    End If
    Let is_char_class be proc string_equals with type_str, "char_class"
    If is_char_class is equal to 1:
        proc generate_char_class with emitter, node
        Return
    End If
    Let is_literal be proc string_equals with type_str, "literal"
    If is_literal is equal to 1:
        proc generate_literal with emitter, node
        Return
    End If
    Let is_anchor be proc string_equals with type_str, "anchor"
    If is_anchor is equal to 1:
        proc generate_anchor with emitter, node
        Return
    End If
    Let is_backreference be proc string_equals with type_str, "backreference"
    If is_backreference is equal to 1:
        proc generate_backreference with emitter, node
        Return
    End If
    Let is_dot be proc string_equals with type_str, "dot"
    If is_dot is equal to 1:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 46
        Return
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Serializes a PCRE alternation by emitting each branch in order with
'|' (124) separators between adjacent branches. No surrounding parens
are emitted; if a parent context needs grouping, it must wrap the
alternation in a group node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Fetches the "branches" list from the node. Walks the list by index;
recurses into generate_node for each branch, then emits '|' iff the
current index is not the last (count-1). Empty/missing branches list
silently produces no output.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_alternation" takes emitter as Integer, node as Integer:
    Let branches_key be proc create_string_literal with "branches"
    Let branches be proc get from Dict with node, branches_key
    If branches is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    Let branch_count be proc size from List with branches
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than branch_count:
        Let branch be proc get from List with branches, i
        proc generate_node with emitter, branch
        If i is less than branch_count minus 1:
            proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 124
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Serializes a PCRE concatenation by emitting each element in sequence
with no separator. This corresponds to the implicit-concatenation
operator in regex syntax.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Fetches the "elements" list from the node. Walks the list by index
and recurses into generate_node for each element. Empty/missing
elements list silently produces no output.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_concatenation" takes emitter as Integer, node as Integer:
    Let elements_key be proc create_string_literal with "elements"
    Let elements be proc get from Dict with node, elements_key
    If elements is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If
    Let element_count be proc size from List with elements
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than element_count:
        Let element be proc get from List with elements, i
        proc generate_node with emitter, element
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Serializes a quantified element by emitting the element followed by
its quantifier suffix. The HIR stores the quantifier as a pre-formed
string (e.g., "*", "+", "?", "{2,5}", "*?", "+?") because the
upstream parser already validated it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads the "element" sub-node and recurses into generate_node. Reads
the "quantifier" string and emits it verbatim. Missing element or
quantifier produces a degenerate but well-formed regex fragment.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_quantified" takes emitter as Integer, node as Integer:
    Let element_key be proc create_string_literal with "element"
    Let element be proc get from Dict with node, element_key
    If element is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_node with emitter, element
    End If
    Let quantifier_key be proc create_string_literal with "quantifier"
    Let quantifier be proc get from Dict with node, quantifier_key
    If quantifier is not equal to 0:
        Let quantifier_str be quantifier
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, quantifier_str
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Serializes a parenthesized group across all seven PCRE flavours:
capturing "(...)", non-capturing "(?:...)", named "(?<name>...)", and
the four zero-width lookaround assertions positive/negative lookahead
"(?=...)"/"(?!...)" and positive/negative lookbehind
"(?<=...)"/"(?<!...)". The HIR encodes the flavour in "group_type" and,
for named groups, the capture name in "name". Each flavour has a fixed
opening delimiter and all close with a single ')'.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads "group_type". "capturing" emits '(' (40). "non_capturing" emits
"(?:". "lookahead_pos" emits "(?=". "lookahead_neg" emits "(?!".
"lookbehind_pos" emits "(?<=". "lookbehind_neg" emits "(?<!". "named"
emits "(?<", the "name" value, then '>'; a named group with no name
falls back to a plain capturing '(' so output stays valid. Any
unrecognised type defaults to '(' for safety. Recurses into the
"contents" sub-node, then unconditionally emits ')' (41).
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_group" takes emitter as Integer, node as Integer:
    Let group_type_key be proc create_string_literal with "group_type"
    Let group_type be proc get from Dict with node, group_type_key
    Let group_type_str be group_type
    Let handled be 0
    Let is_capturing be proc string_equals with group_type_str, "capturing"
    If is_capturing is equal to 1:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 40
        Set handled to 1
    End If
    If handled is equal to 0:
        Let is_non_capturing be proc string_equals with group_type_str, "non_capturing"
        If is_non_capturing is equal to 1:
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "(?:"
            Set handled to 1
        End If
    End If
    If handled is equal to 0:
        Let is_lah_pos be proc string_equals with group_type_str, "lookahead_pos"
        If is_lah_pos is equal to 1:
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "(?="
            Set handled to 1
        End If
    End If
    If handled is equal to 0:
        Let is_lah_neg be proc string_equals with group_type_str, "lookahead_neg"
        If is_lah_neg is equal to 1:
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "(?!"
            Set handled to 1
        End If
    End If
    If handled is equal to 0:
        Let is_lbh_pos be proc string_equals with group_type_str, "lookbehind_pos"
        If is_lbh_pos is equal to 1:
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "(?<="
            Set handled to 1
        End If
    End If
    If handled is equal to 0:
        Let is_lbh_neg be proc string_equals with group_type_str, "lookbehind_neg"
        If is_lbh_neg is equal to 1:
            proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "(?<!"
            Set handled to 1
        End If
    End If
    If handled is equal to 0:
        Let is_named be proc string_equals with group_type_str, "named"
        If is_named is equal to 1:
            Let name_key be proc create_string_literal with "name"
            Let name_value be proc get from Dict with node, name_key
            If name_value is not equal to 0:
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, "(?<"
                proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, name_value
                proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 62
            Otherwise:
                proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 40
            End If
            Set handled to 1
        End If
    End If
    If handled is equal to 0:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 40
    End If
    Let contents_key be proc create_string_literal with "contents"
    Let contents be proc get from Dict with node, contents_key
    If contents is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_node with emitter, contents
    End If
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 41
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a character class. The HIR stores the entire bracketed class
expression (including brackets, negation prefix, ranges) as a single
pre-formed "value" string because parsing already validated it; this
proc just blits it.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads "value" and emits it verbatim; null value emits nothing.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_char_class" takes emitter as Integer, node as Integer:
    Let value_key be proc create_string_literal with "value"
    Let value be proc get from Dict with node, value_key
    If value is not equal to 0:
        Let value_str be value
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, value_str
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a literal sequence (a run of non-special characters). The HIR
stores it as a pre-escaped "value" string so this proc need not know
which characters require backslash escaping.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads "value" and emits it verbatim; null value emits nothing.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_literal" takes emitter as Integer, node as Integer:
    Let value_key be proc create_string_literal with "value"
    Let value be proc get from Dict with node, value_key
    If value is not equal to 0:
        Let value_str be value
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, value_str
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a positional anchor (^, $, \b, \B, \A, \Z, \z). The HIR stores
the literal anchor string in "value" because the set is small and
fixed.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads "value" and emits it verbatim; null value emits nothing.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_anchor" takes emitter as Integer, node as Integer:
    Let value_key be proc create_string_literal with "value"
    Let value be proc get from Dict with node, value_key
    If value is not equal to 0:
        Let value_str be value
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, value_str
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits a backreference such as \1, \k<name>, or \g{n}. The HIR stores
the formed reference syntax in "value" so this proc only blits.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Reads "value" and emits it verbatim; null value emits nothing.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_backreference" takes emitter as Integer, node as Integer:
    Let value_key be proc create_string_literal with "value"
    Let value be proc get from Dict with node, value_key
    If value is not equal to 0:
        Let value_str be value
        proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, value_str
    End If
End Process

@Reasoning:
Local null-terminated string compare. Inlined here instead of importing
the StringCore variant to avoid pulling in a dependency for the type
dispatcher's hot path.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Walks both strings byte-by-byte using memory_get_byte. Returns 0
immediately on the first mismatch. Returns 1 when both bytes are NUL
(0), confirming the strings have the same length and content. Uses
"While 1 is equal to 1" as a sentinel-free infinite loop because the
terminating NUL is the loop's natural exit.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(n) in the shorter string's length. No allocation.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "string_equals" takes str1 as String, str2 as String returns Integer:
    Let i be 0
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let c1 be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with str1, i
        Let c2 be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with str2, i
        If c1 is not equal to c2:
            Return 0
        End If
        If c1 is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Local alias for StringCore.create_string_from_literal. Kept as a
one-liner wrapper because the dispatcher reads better with the
shorter local name "create_string_literal" at every call site.
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_string_literal" takes value as String returns Integer:
    Return proc create_from_literal from StringCore with value
End Process
